## Module: `tests/helpers.ts`

This module provides shared test infrastructure consumed by every `describe` group.

### Exported Types

```typescript
export interface TestContext {
  program: Program;
  connection: Connection;
  operator: Keypair;
  customer: Keypair;
  author: Keypair;
  secondCustomer: Keypair;
  secondAuthor: Keypair;
  mint: PublicKey;
  treasuryAta: PublicKey;
  customerAta: PublicKey;
  authorAta: PublicKey;
  vaultPda: PublicKey;
  operatorConfigPda: PublicKey;
}

export interface PdaResult {
  pda: PublicKey;
  bump: number;
}
```

### PDA Derivation Functions

All PDA helpers must match on-chain seed logic exactly.

| Function | Seeds | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `deriveOperatorConfigPda(programId)` | `[b"operator_config"]` | Singleton |
| `deriveCustomerPda(customer, programId)` | `[b"customer_balance", customer.toBytes()]` | Per-customer |
| `derivePackagePda(packageId, programId)` | `[b"agent_package", SHA256(packageId)]` | SHA-256 hash |
| `deriveReceiptPda(taskId, programId)` | `[b"task_receipt", SHA256(taskId)]` | SHA-256 hash |
| `deriveVaultPda(mint, programId)` | `[b"vault", mint.toBytes()]` | Per-mint vault |

### SHA-256 Hashing
```typescript
import { createHash } from "crypto";
export function hashSeed(input: string): Buffer {
  return createHash("sha256").update(input).digest();
}
```
This **must** produce identical bytes to the on-chain `hash_seed` in `utils/mod.rs`.

### Token Helpers
- `createMockMint(connection, payer, decimals=6)` → `PublicKey` — uses `@solana/spl-token.createMint`.
- `createAta(connection, payer, mint, owner)` → `PublicKey` — uses `createAssociatedTokenAccount`.
- `mintTo(connection, payer, mint, ata, amount)` → `void` — mints tokens.
- `airdropSol(connection, pubkey, amount)` → `void` — confirms airdrop.

### Implementation Notes
- All helpers are `async` and await confirmation.
- PDA derivation is synchronous (`PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync`).
- The `hashSeed` function returns a 32-byte `Buffer` used directly in `findProgramAddressSync` seeds array.

